  , issueBody =
      Just
        "We currently don't provide any guidance on what the #shards and #replicas values mean, or what reasonable values are.\n\nI think we should have a short help text in the reconfiguration dialog explaining that replication is for data safety, and sharding for performance.\nI think we should also state that at least 3 replicas are required to enable automatic failover, and that you need at least 2 replicas per shard to avoid data loss in case of a server failure.\n\nIn addition to this short introduction we might want to link to an appropriate page in our documentation, e.g. http://rethinkdb.com/docs/sharding-and-replication/\n"
